evidence: Then the photomultiplier tubes convert the light into an electrical signal...

concepts.term: nuclear imaging is highly complementary to X-ray imaging

evidence: The purpose of the collimator is to make sure that the signals we detect are aligned with the holes. That way, any photon recorded must have come from directly beneath that hole, and this gives us the spatial information we need.

triples.evidence: Once the gamma photon passes through the collimator, it hits the scintillation crystal.
